<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="375" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1436,151,790]" pageId="14" pageNumber="375">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,726,752]" pageId="14" pageNumber="375">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other species of this genus by having median clypeal lobe weak (
<figureCitation box="[226,309,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,453,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-121@13.[163,1425,453,1923]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Bethylus ningxicus sp. nov. holotype, ♂. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Forewing; h. The seventh metasomal sternum and Hypopygium; i. Genitalia, dorsal view; j. Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775753/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="375">Fig. 7b</figureCitation>
), median notch of hypopygium deep and narrow (
<figureCitation box="[869,952,763,790]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[163,1425,453,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-121@13.[163,1425,453,1923]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 7. Bethylus ningxicus sp. nov. holotype, ♂. a. Habitus lateral; b. Head, frontal view; c. Mandible; d. Antenna; e. Head, lateral view; f. Mesosoma, dorsal view; g. Forewing; h. The seventh metasomal sternum and Hypopygium; i. Genitalia, dorsal view; j. Genitalia, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.15 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4775753" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4775753/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="375">Fig. 7h</figureCitation>
), and apical margin of cuspis rounded.
</paragraph>
